author: Telegraph Staff
title: Agincourt - and 10 more great victories against the odds
text:
To mark the 600th anniversary of the remarkable English triumph at Agincourt in 1415 , here are 10 more great victories against the odds. 
-- 
David and Goliath 
The giant Philistine warrior was felled by a stone flung by the young David, future king of Israel, according to the Bible story. 
Pictured above is Goliath House in Regensburg, Germany. Built in 1260, the mural depicting the fight between David and Goliath was added in 1573. The Bavarian city of Regensburg is the oldest city on the Danube and known as Germany's "medieval miracle". Picture: Alamy
